<div id="main">

<h1>URL filtering</h1>
<h2>Description</h2>
<p>This patch adds URL filtering support to surf, for example to remove
advertisements. The file <code>filters</code> contains POSIX regular expressions (see the
<code>re_format(7)</code> manpage). If a HTTP request is about to be made for a URL that
matches any of the expressions in the file, it is replaced with <code>about:blank</code>
instead. This may lead to slightly broken display on pages that expect e.g.
images to load correctly. The impact is negligible though.</p>
<h2>Example</h2>
<p>An example list of filters looks like this:</p>
<pre><code>/favicon\.ico$
eviladvertismentcompany\.{net,com}/ads
</code></pre>
<h2>Download</h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="surf-tip-url-filtering.diff">surf-tip-url-filtering.diff</a> (4176) (20141014)</li>
</ul>
